
jMax

(C) Copyright Ircam 1994, 1995, 1998, 1999, 2002


Introduction

jMax is a visual programming environment 
for real-time, interactive multimedia applications. 


Documentation

jMax documentation is included in this distribution, under
doc subdirectory. It is in HTML format. The root file
of the documentation is doc/index.html.

________________________________________________________________________________
Installation and compilation

For Linux platform:
	
See INSTALL.linux

For MacOSX platform:

The jMaxProject.pbproj, that you can find in "jmax/macosxbuild/jMaxProject/", 
is generated with ProjectBuilder Version 2.0.1 (July 2002 Developer Tools).
     
Just build the "all" target in jMaxProject. If build succeeded you will 
find jMax.app in "jmax/macosxbuild/jMaxProject/build/".
Now you can move it and install it were you want.

